2364417248242112556.Text: Fedris Hler has told me to investigate the source of the attacks on the city. A passageway to an underground Dwemer ruin has opened in the Plaza, and I am to explore the area and report to Drin as soon as I have information on the creatures' origin. The entrance is in the ruins of the Memorial Statue.

927214446574517373.Text: Delitian knows I have reported the attack to Hler, and he would also like me to investigate the source of the attacks. He suggests that I should report the findings to him, as it is a concern for the Empire.

1640164102351419616.Text: Tienius Delitian has told me to investigate the source of the attacks on the city. A passageway to an underground Dwemer ruin has opened in the Plaza, and I am to explore the area and report to Delitian as soon as I have information on the creatures' origin. The entrance is in the ruins of the Memorial Statue.

1639619465707620173.Text: Hler has heard that I reported the attack to Tienius Delitian. He would also like me to investigate the source of the attacks, but he believes this is a matter for the Temple to deal with.

222126649249644522.Text: I have witnessed Dwemer constructs and these mysterious new Fabricant creatures battling in the ruins of Bamz-Amschend. The Dwemer creatures seemed to be defending the ruins against the intruding constructs. Their origin is still a mystery to me, but it is clear that they are not of Dwemer make. I should report my findings immediately.

293632049216424945.Text: I have reported to Tienius Delitian about the fight I witnessed in the ruins of Bamz-Amschend. He tells me the King would like to speak with me.

357425717228138288.Text: I have reported to Fedris Hler about the fight I witnessed in the ruins of Bamz-Amschend. I should relay the information to Almalexia.
